-- ACR Capital Holdings to Sell 22 Percent Stake to Marubeni
-- B y   C a t h y   C h a n
-- 2012-04-20T04:45:10Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-20/acr-capital-holdings-to-sell-22-percent-stake-to-marubeni.html
ACR Capital Holdings Pte. , the
insurance company that counts counts Singapore’s Temasek
Holdings Pte. as its major shareholder, said  Marubeni Corp. (8002)  will
buy a 22 percent stake in the company to provide new business
opportunities.  The deal will help Marubeni grow in the insurance sector,
the Japanese company said today in a statement released by
Singapore-based ACR. ACR controls Asia Capital Reinsurance
Group. Marubeni has reinsurance-related businesses in  Tokyo ,
Singapore and  London .  The companies didn’t disclose the value of the transaction.
Nikkei earlier reported Marubeni’s purchase was valued at $250
million.  ACR was established in 2006 and has a presence in Hong
Kong, Taiwan,  Japan , Korea,  India  and Vietnam. Its other major
shareholders include  3i Group Plc (III)  and Khazanah Nasional Bhd.,
ACR said.  Barclays Plc advised ACR on the sale.  To contact the reporter on this story:
